# revitify ⇄ graphify upstream tracking
# Revitify adapts CONCEPTS from graphify (MIT) with an original TypeScript implementation and the
# same output contract (graphify-out/: graph.json · graph.html · GRAPH_REPORT.md).
# This file pins HOW FAR upstream we have looked, so future fixes can be ported deliberately:
# review upstream commits/PRs SINCE the pin below, port what matters, then move the pin.

upstream_repo   = https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify
upstream_clone  = _ref/reference/graphify   (shallow, reference only)

# Last upstream state our implementation corresponds to:
synced_commit   = 1bb30fcc567a72280f4dc1763947140268f101c5
synced_version  = 0.8.38
synced_at       = 2026-06-12
last_merged_pr  = #1271 (2026-06-11) feat(extract): add opt-in --cargo crate dependency extractor

# Output-contract anchor (what Rivet's loadCodeGraph was verified against): v0.8.37 graph.json —
# nodes[{id,name,label,source_file,source_location,community}], links[{source,target,relation}],
# built_at_commit. Any upstream change to this shape is a MUST-port.

# Sync ritual:
#   1. cd _ref/reference/graphify && git fetch --depth 50 origin && git log --oneline <synced_commit>..origin/HEAD
#   2. gh api repos/safishamsi/graphify/pulls?state=closed — review merged PRs since last_merged_pr
#   3. Port relevant fixes into packages/revitify (through Rivet's own loop, tests first)
#   4. Update synced_commit / synced_version / last_merged_pr / synced_at here, same commit
